  "text": "Following surgery, the animal was placed in a sound-attenuated room with the head secured to a post on the vibration isolation frame. The sound-treated room was made anechoic for frequencies above 625 Hz with acoustic wedges (Sonex 3″) covering walls and exposed portions of the vibration isolation frame, equipment and floor. Prior to acute recordings, peripheral hearing sensitivity was determined from auditory brainstem response (ABR) thresholds at frequencies of 2, 3, 4, 6, 10, 12, 16 and 20 kHz (for details, see [CITATION_1] .",
